<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><p><a href="http://www.ck-blog.com/.shared/image.html?/photos/uncategorized/2008/11/01/6a00d83451bafe69e2010535c10619970c.jpg" onclick="window.open(this.href, '_blank', 'width=300,height=373,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0'); return false"><img width="300" height="373" border="0" alt="6a00d83451bafe69e2010535c10619970c" title="6a00d83451bafe69e2010535c10619970c" src="http://www.ck-blog.com/cks_blog/images/2008/11/01/6a00d83451bafe69e2010535c10619970c.jpg" style="margin: 0px 0px 5px 5px; float: right;" /></a>

A year and a half ago, an online conversation between two marketing
professionals in the U.S. and Australia evolved into a collaborative
writing effort by more than 100 bloggers from nine countries contributing content (via 400-word chapters) that created a book called The Age of Conversation... and I was one of those proud authors.</p>

<p>The project raised
nearly $15,000 for Variety, the international children's charity.&nbsp; 

</p>

<p>
Following the success of the first book, which was published in the
summer of 2007, <a href="http://www.drewsmarketingminute.com">Drew McLellan</a> and<a href="http://www.servantofchaos.com"> Gavin Heaton</a>, organizers of the first
project, have now published <span style="font-size: 1.2em;"><strong>Age of Conversation 2</strong></span>, which compiles
written thoughts on the role of&nbsp; conversation in marketing today <span style="font-size: 1.4em;"><strong>from
237 marketing professionals</strong></span> who blog in the U.S. and 15 other
countries... and once again, I'm proud to be one of those authors.<br />
</p>

<p><strong>Pricing for The Age of Conversation 2 is as follows (with all proceeds going to charity, no author is profiting from this collaborative venture):</strong>


</p>

<ul><li>
e-book: $12.50&nbsp; ($10.00 going to charity)</li>

<li>
paperback book: $19.95 ($8.02 to charity)</li>

<li>
hardback book: $29.95 ($4.60 to charity)</li></ul>
<p>
