</div>]]></content:encoded><description>A year and a half ago, an online conversation between two marketing professionals in the U.S. and Australia evolved into a collaborative writing effort by more than 100 bloggers from nine countries contributing content (via 400-word chapters) that created a book called The Age of Conversation... and I was one of those proud authors. The project raised nearly $15,000 for Variety, the international children's charity. Following the success of the first book, which was published in the summer of 2007, Drew McLellan and Gavin Heaton, organizers of the first project, have now published Age of Conversation 2, which compiles written thoughts on the role of conversation in marketing today from 237 marketing professionals who blog in the U.S. and 15 other countries... and once again, I'm proud to be one of those authors. Pricing for The Age of Conversation 2 is as follows (with all proceeds going to charity, no author is profiting from this collaborative venture): e-book: $12.50 ($10.00 going to charity) paperback book: $19.95 ($8.02 to charity) hardback book: $29.95 ($4.60 to charity) Purchases can be made at www.lulu.com/ageofconversationBios of all authors located hereLinks to all authors' blogs after the jump if you're reading this on my blog (otherwise the list is part of the full post if you're reading this in RSS or email form). Adrian Ho, Aki Spicer, Alex Henault, Amy Jussel, Andrew Odom, Andy Nulman, Andy Sernovitz, Andy Whitlock, Angela Maiers, Ann Handley, Anna Farmery, Armando Alves, Arun Rajagopal, Asi Sharabi, Becky Carroll, Becky McCray, Bernie Scheffler, Bill Gammell, Bob LeDrew, Brad Shorr, Brandon Murphy, Branislav Peric, Brent Dixon, Brett Macfarlane, Brian Reich, C.C. Chapman, Cam Beck, Casper Willer, Cathleen Rittereiser, Cathryn Hrudicka, Cedric Giorgi, Charles Sipe, Chris Kieff, Chris Cree, Chris Wilson, Christina Kerley (CK), C.B. Whittemore, Chris Brown, Connie Bensen, Connie Reece, Corentin Monot, Craig Wilson