estion "How has marketing changed with the 'new guard' of social media?" And this segment (running at 3:17 minutes) focuses on the question "With so many social media tools available to entrepreneurs and startups, how to decide which tool is best for your company?" Again, the entire video series (9 segments) is here. RSS and email subscribers please click through to the blog to view them.</description><feedburner:origLink>http://www.ck-blog.com/cks_blog/2008/09/talking-social.html</feedburner:origLink></item><item><title>Bye Bye Big Apple, I'm heading West...</title><link>http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/ck-Blog/~3/398241062/bye-bye-big-app.html</link><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">CK (Christina Kerley)</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 29 Sep 2008 20:44:15 -0500</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:typepad.com,2003:post-55902210</guid><content:encoded xmlns:content="http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/"><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://www.ck-blog.com/.shared/image.html?/photos/uncategorized/2008/09/20/ck125x125.gif" onclick="window.open(this.href, '_blank', 'width=125,height=125,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0'); return false"><img width="150" height="150" border="0" alt="Ck125x125" title="Ck125x125" src="http://www.ck-blog.com/cks_blog/images/2008/09/20/ck125x125.gif" style="margin: 0px 5px 5px 0px; float: left;"></img></a>
I'll be on the road this week seeing great spots in this great country. Yep, I'm leaving NYC and heading West. And then I'm going to keep heading more West until I hit the coast. Perhaps I'll be inspired to dip a toe into the Pacific Ocean.<br> </p>

<p>First I'll be in Columbus, Ohio for the SBMU Conference (<a href="http://unleashed.smallbusinessanswers.com/2008/columbus/">Small Business Marketing Unleashed</a>) from Sunday until Wednesday where I'll be talking Branding and Social Media--which just so happen to be TWO of my favorite subjects ;-).<br> </p>

<p>I've <a href="http://www.ck-blog.com/cks_blog/2008/08/a-different-kin.html">written before</a> about what I'll be covering at the conference and you can find out much more about SBMU <a href="http://unleashed.smallbusinessanswers.com/2008/columbus/">right here.</a> If you're attending, I can't wait to meet you and grok about marketing.</p>





<p><a onclick="window.open(this.href, '_blank', 'width=800,height=1072,scrollbars=no,resizable=no,toolbar=no,directories=no,location=no,menubar=no,status=no,left=0,top=0'); return false" href="http://www.ck-blog.com/.shared/image.html?/photos/uncategorized/2008/09/20/invitation_3.jpg"><img width="200" height="268" border="0" src="http://www.ck-blog.com/cks_blog/images/2008/09/20/invitation_3.jpg" title="Invitation_3" alt="Invitation_3" style="margin: 0px 0px 5px 5px; float: right;"></img></a> Come Thursday I'll move from the Midwest to the West Coast. If you're in San Francisco and free for lunch on Thursday (9/25, from 12-2p) why not join me and many other 
technology and social media professionals at a <a href="http://tinyurl.com/3pxtpv">launch luncheon for Glubble's New Edition for Families</a>. Oh how fun it is to look at technology NOT from the standpoint of a marketer or adult...but as a family with kids under age 12.</p>



<p>In fact, it makes me want to be a kid again and focus on playing games not devising grown-up strategies, chatting online with my cousins instead of emailing clients--and creating works of art through coloring pages instead of creating charts. Oh to be a kid again with nary a care in the world. </p>

<p>The <a href="http://tinyurl.com/3pxtpv">information is here</a> and if you want to attend please send an email to Liana at <a href="mailto:Liana@vinebergcommunications.com">this email address</a>. Just tell her that CK sent you and that you, too, wish you could be a kid again (if only for one day).</p>

